    "en": {
      "title": "50,000 Ukrainian refugees are homeless in Britain",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "50,000 Ukrainian refugees are said to be facing homelessness in the UK.",
        "As many as 50,000 Ukrainians could become homeless in the UK next year as the government's scheme to match refugees with British families collapses, The Guardian reported. With the cost of living rising rapidly, the opposition wants the government to increase payments to host families.",
        "Between 15,000 and 21,000 Ukrainians could be homeless by winter, and more than 50,000 by mid-2023, according to an analysis by the Labor Party, the Liberal Democrats and children's charity Barnardos, based on feedback from British hosts, the newspaper said. reports."
